@NM: I'm going to guess you're talking about my point on your <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6832029#p6832029">45</a>. It's a hidden warning that town wasn't supposed to see as warning.<br>
<br>
I should add, with MM now saying (late though!) he's in so many other games, this 45 could make sense but then again, MM could have told NM about that before the game started and NM used that to cover up the slip. I'm stuck in a tunnel, I keep seeing scummotivation with both of them.

Why wouldn't you? If you are town, you are kinda relying on town to come to a decision about lynches anyway? <br>
<br>
@Far, I tend to be a bit 'black or white' in my thinking occasionally (e.g. If x is mafia, y has to be scum), but could you explain your vote more?

Wow. Seriously. Not even is it in the rules, but I have actually accused NM and Monkey of a PT-slip because of daytalk. But I do think scum would check to see whether they're talking about the correct game. Difficult. <br>
<br>
@Bella, I don't know. I was sharing my thoughts but I'm still null on Rev. What do you mean by the wagon looks more town? I think I was pretty clear that I thought Kaboose was scum because of the resistance, so I'm thinking you mean town is voting for Kaboose. To give you an answer I'd have to reread the reasons for voting for Kaboose. I'll do that later because I have a headache from hitting my head pretty hard this morning.

@Skold, why you so bothered about bbt??<br>
<br>
(OOC: Wanderer, I hope your head feels better, everyone enjoy(ed)(s) their bdays this week and skold/bbt are having fun with academic nonsense)

